        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">I think this has been gone over a thousand times...<BR>This is what I think about fear from what I've read and my own observations etc...</P><P>1) you cast fear<BR>2) there is a mathmatical equation depending on your lvl, the mobs lvl and the mobs magic resist<BR>4) depending on this equation, there is basically a role(random) with odds on whether it will stick or resist. example: blue con, using invoke fear, with a mr of 100 might have odds of 1/20 of resisting(these are just made up numbers for the sake of example)<BR>3) *if* fear sticks the mob begins to run<BR>4) every 6 seconds (or 1 tick) the mob has a chance to break that fear<BR>5) what depends on whether the mob breaks the fear is a similiar equation to whether it originally sticks; its MR, the fear you use and the lvl you were when you cast it on the mob<BR>6) this happens until the max duration of the fear, when it then automatically wears off</P><P>These are my own observations from what I've seen and what I've read. I've both had positive charisma and (now)way negative charisma.</P><P>Wish I knew for sure, I could be totally off base. I'm not an EQ coder so can't positively confirm any of this.</P><P>Gylgesh Gloomtouch,<BR>54th Necro of the Heroic Few<BR>Morell-Thule<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
